		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />L and R unfortunately map to the mouse's speed report. But the entire first byte is normally all 0s: the only question is whether any existing software cares or if it all ignores it.<br /><br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/Mouse">http://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/Mouse</a><!-- m --> ; <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://wiki.superfamicom.org/snes/show/Controllers#mouse">http://wiki.superfamicom.org/snes/show/ ... lers#mouse</a><!-- m --> ; <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://problemkaputt.de/fullsnes.htm#snescontrollersmousetwobuttonmouse">http://problemkaputt.de/fullsnes.htm#sn ... uttonmouse</a><!-- m -->

		

